I'm a step away
from giving you

02:44.435 --> 02:46.136
a bag of sugar and a spoon.

02:46.170 --> 02:51.475
I'm just saying, we don't have
to force ourselves to do this.

02:51.509 --> 02:53.477
What, eat?

02:53.511 --> 02:55.061
At the table.

02:55.096 --> 02:57.180
Together every night.

02:59.049 --> 03:00.801
You used to eat
with your mother, right?

03:00.835 --> 03:02.352
When I wasn't here?

03:02.386 --> 03:04.571
Yeah, usually.

03:04.605 --> 03:06.723
What did she have to do

03:06.741 --> 03:08.358
to convince you
to sit down with her?

03:08.392 --> 03:10.911
I don't know.

03:10.945 --> 03:14.498
I guess she cooked actual food.

03:20.505 --> 03:21.788
What's all that?

03:21.839 --> 03:23.089
Mail.

03:23.124 --> 03:24.508
Rex's.

03:24.542 --> 03:28.011
That was Cole's dad.

03:28.045 --> 03:30.430
Apparently Rex has been having
stuff shipped to their address.

03:30.464 --> 03:32.549
Look at this.

03:32.583 --> 03:34.417
Catalogs.

03:34.435 --> 03:36.853
Junk mail.

03:36.888 --> 03:39.890
This one looks like a bill.

03:39.924 --> 03:42.425
Could you pass me a knife?

03:44.061 --> 03:45.762
Why?

03:45.780 --> 03:47.230
I want to open the box,

03:47.264 --> 03:48.615
see what's inside.

03:52.403 --> 03:53.620
Can we just...

03:53.654 --> 03:55.622
Can we leave that alone?

03:55.656 --> 03:57.791
Why?

03:57.825 --> 04:00.410
Because I-I...

04:00.444 --> 04:03.129
What's the point?

04:03.164 --> 04:07.116
Well, aren't you curious
to see what it is?

04:07.134 --> 04:08.501
I mean, he's having
stuff shipped

04:08.553 --> 04:10.136
to somebody else's house.

04:10.171 --> 04:12.005
All right, fine.

04:12.056 --> 04:14.140
Can you just leave it
till I go?

04:14.175 --> 04:15.976
What's wrong?

04:16.010 --> 04:18.478
I'm not like you.

04:18.512 --> 04:21.147
Okay, I...

04:23.184 --> 04:27.487
Yesterday, I found his cleat
in the trunk of the car,

04:27.521 --> 04:31.741
and I... I remember
he'd lost it,

04:31.776 --> 04:34.494
Yeah. and he'd been
looking for it for weeks,

04:34.528 --> 04:37.831
and I found it.

04:37.865 --> 04:41.785
And I just stood there, and I...

04:41.819 --> 04:44.371
It just about put me
on the ground.

04:44.422 --> 04:45.505
So, we'll...

04:45.539 --> 04:47.123
we'll go through
his mail, I just...

04:47.157 --> 04:49.158
Shh.

04:54.832 --> 04:56.833
I'm sorry.

05:00.221 --> 05:02.505
I don't understand
how it's so easy for you.

05:05.276 --> 05:07.143
It-It's not that
it's easy for me.

05:07.177 --> 05:09.529
I just... sometimes things,

05:09.563 --> 05:12.699
they don't remind me
of him being gone,

05:12.733 --> 05:14.985
or the accident, they...

05:15.019 --> 05:17.787
they remind me of him,

05:17.822 --> 05:20.323
you know?

05:20.357 --> 05:23.043
I mean, I don't
know what's in there,

05:23.077 --> 05:27.163
but on the off chance it might
have made you think of him,

05:27.197 --> 05:31.367
in case it put a
smile on your face...

05:33.387 --> 05:35.672
I thought it was
worth opening.

05:35.706 --> 05:37.724
I'm sorry.

05:37.758 --> 05:40.343
No.

05:40.377 --> 05:43.013
It just...

05:43.047 --> 05:45.048
doesn't work like that for me.

05:53.324 --> 05:55.992
<i>Why do you think
that you and your wife</i>

05:56.027 --> 05:57.226
have such different reactions

05:57.244 --> 05:58.995
when something reminds you
of Rex?

06:03.951 --> 06:06.336
Sometimes I...

06:06.370 --> 06:07.871
Sometimes I think
she's trying to deal

06:07.905 --> 06:10.340
with the fact that he's gone
by pretending he was never here.

06:10.374 --> 06:13.677
Where as you simply
insist on pretending

06:13.711 --> 06:15.428
that he's perfectly fine.

06:15.463 --> 06:18.915
I know you want
to hold on to your son,

06:18.933 --> 06:21.601
but have you considered the
possibility that that fantasy

06:21.635 --> 06:25.722
may become incompatible
with holding on to your wife?

06:25.756 --> 06:29.059
Just because I have
a different perspective,

06:29.093 --> 06:32.762
I don't see that as a bad thing.

06:32.797 --> 06:35.264
Maybe the fact that I
see things differently

06:35.282 --> 06:37.033
allows me to know
what questions to ask,

06:37.068 --> 06:38.451
what answers to focus on.

06:38.486 --> 06:41.237
Maybe it puts me
in a better position to help.

06:46.727 --> 06:48.244
What?

06:48.278 --> 06:51.280
Number three, Bernard Mackenzie.

06:51.298 --> 06:53.299
What do you know about that?

06:53.334 --> 06:55.001
Some dead homeless guy.

06:55.052 --> 06:56.319
Why?

06:56.354 --> 06:57.804
Dr. Bernard Mackenzie's

06:57.838 --> 06:59.222
death is now
officially a murder.

06:59.256 --> 07:00.974
Let me see the file.

07:01.008 --> 07:02.926
But they worked it.
It's, you know,

07:02.960 --> 07:05.345
there's no evidence,
no leads, it's a dead end.

07:05.396 --> 07:06.796
Why are you so interested

07:06.814 --> 07:09.065
in a dead homeless guy?

07:10.101 --> 07:12.068
Just get me the file.

07:12.103 --> 07:14.070
All right.

07:14.105 --> 07:15.772
<i>I think</i>

07:15.806 --> 07:18.491
that these sorts of connections
between your worlds can be

07:18.526 --> 07:20.593
<i>incredibly beneficial,</i>
<i>and I support</i>

07:20.628 --> 07:22.062
<i>a more active connection</i>

07:22.096 --> 07:25.481
<i>between your conscious</i>
<i>and unconscious mind.</i>

07:25.499 --> 07:29.452
<i>I think it's gonna aid you</i>
<i>in uncovering and processing</i>

07:29.486 --> 07:31.671
<i>the source</i>
<i>of your emotional issues.</i>

07:33.958 --> 07:36.292
Well,

07:36.326 --> 07:38.511
would it surprise
you to hear Dr. Lee

07:38.546 --> 07:40.964
feels slightly differently?

07:40.998 --> 07:43.633
Let me be clear, Detective.

07:43.667 --> 07:47.670
Your condition is the result
of a deeply fractured psyche.

07:47.688 --> 07:49.355
<i>It is a problem.</i>

07:49.390 --> 07:53.176
<i>It is not a tool.</i>

07:53.194 --> 07:57.147
<i>Well, you can call it
whatever you like, Doctor.</i>

07:57.181 --> 08:00.183
I seem to be doing all right
with it.

